<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="355" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,223,429]" pageId="14" pageNumber="355">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,223,249]" pageId="14" pageNumber="355">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The venter of the body is black, except the mesosternum is mediolaterally with a yellowish-brown mark, the abdomen is posteriorly yellow; the flexor region of the fore femur of male almost medially with a shallow notch; the proctiger of the male is subovate (
<bibRefCitation author="Tran, A. D. &amp; Polhemus, D. A." box="[655,923,295,321]" pageId="14" pageNumber="355" pagination="109 - 149" refId="ref11952" refString="Tran, A. D. &amp; Polhemus, D. A. (2017) The genus Metrocoris Mayr, 1865 (Gerromorpha: Gerridae) in Vietnam, with descriptions of five new species. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 65, 109 - 149." type="journal article" year="2017">Tran &amp; Polhemus 2017</bibRefCitation>
, Fig. 109); the paramere is falciform (
<bibRefCitation author="Tran, A. D. &amp; Polhemus, D. A." pageId="14" pageNumber="355" pagination="109 - 149" refId="ref11952" refString="Tran, A. D. &amp; Polhemus, D. A. (2017) The genus Metrocoris Mayr, 1865 (Gerromorpha: Gerridae) in Vietnam, with descriptions of five new species. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 65, 109 - 149." type="journal article" year="2017">Tran &amp; Polhemus 2017</bibRefCitation>
, Figs. 110, 111); the ventral sclerite is short (
<bibRefCitation author="Tran, A. D. &amp; Polhemus, D. A." box="[830,1096,331,357]" pageId="14" pageNumber="355" pagination="109 - 149" refId="ref11952" refString="Tran, A. D. &amp; Polhemus, D. A. (2017) The genus Metrocoris Mayr, 1865 (Gerromorpha: Gerridae) in Vietnam, with descriptions of five new species. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 65, 109 - 149." type="journal article" year="2017">Tran &amp; Polhemus 2017</bibRefCitation>
, Fig. 113).
</paragraph>
